## Functions

### advanceToNextLeafType() {#ac45bdcc05a92d63f2249f476eeb17e77}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool advanceToNextLeafType (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/type">Type</a> &#42; &gt; &amp; SubTypes, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; unsigned &gt; &amp; Path)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Move the given iterators to the next leaf type in depth first traversal.

Performs a depth-first traversal of the type as specified by its arguments, stopping at the next leaf node (which may be a legitimate scalar type or an empty struct or array).


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="SubTypes">List of the partial components making up the type from outermost to innermost non-empty aggregate. The element currently represented is SubTypes.back()-&gt;getTypeAtIndex(Path.back() - 1).</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Path">Set of extractvalue indices leading from the outermost type (SubTypes&#91;0&#93;) to the leaf node currently represented.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
true if a new type was found, false otherwise. Calling this function again on a finished iterator will repeatedly return false. SubTypes.back()-&gt;getTypeAtIndex(Path.back()) is either an empty aggregate or a non-aggregate
</SectionUser>

Definition at line <a href="#l00445">445</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/analysis-cpp">Analysis.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### firstRealType() {#a455039cd6aa5d034220ca078a6b6c30e}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool firstRealType (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/type">Type</a> &#42; Next, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/type">Type</a> &#42; &gt; &amp; SubTypes, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; unsigned &gt; &amp; Path)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Find the first non-empty, scalar-like type in Next and setup the iterator components.

Assuming Next is an aggregate of some kind, this function will traverse the tree from left to right (i.e. depth-first) looking for the first non-aggregate type which will play a role in function return.

For example, if Next was &#123;&#91;0 x i64&#93;, &#123;&#123;&#125;, i32, &#123;&#125;&#125;, i32&#125; then we would setup Path as &#91;1, 1&#93; and SubTypes as &#91;Next, &#123;&#123;&#125;, i32, &#123;&#125;&#125;&#93; to represent the first i32 in that type.

Definition at line <a href="#l00486">486</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/analysis-cpp">Analysis.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### getNoopInput() {#ade3b3b604b9b365a57f791ab198a691a}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static const Value &#42; getNoopInput (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42; V, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; unsigned &gt; &amp; ValLoc, unsigned &amp; DataBits, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetloweringbase">TargetLoweringBase</a> &amp; TLI, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/datalayout">DataLayout</a> &amp; DL)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Look through operations that will be free to find the earliest source of this value.

<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="ValLoc">If V has aggregate type, we will be interested in a particular scalar component. This records its address; the reverse of this list gives a sequence of indices appropriate for an extractvalue to locate the important value. This value is updated during the function and on exit will indicate similar information for the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> returned.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="DataBits">If this function looks through truncate instructions, this will record the smallest size attained.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"></CodeLine>
